data.title: Brownell Memorial Park & Carillon Tower
data.meta_description: A 9.5 acre park in a natural setting located next to Lake Palourde. The 106 ft. tall carillon tower contains 61 bronze bells, which were cast in Holland. Bells play two selections every 15 minutes. The park is a designated bird sanctuary and a must for naturalists and photography buffs. With advance notice, a Wildlife & Fisheries agent can accompany your group to answer questions and give facts on the area's wildlife, flora and fauna.
